[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A timeout error has been detected during fuzzing operations using libFuzzer. This   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         indicates that the fuzzer encountered an execution path that exceeded the           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         configured timeout threshold, suggesting the presence of code that can hang or      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         execute for an abnormally long time when processing certain inputs.                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Issue Overview                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The error [32m"libFuzzer: timeout"[0m indicates that during automated fuzzing testing, the [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         execution of the target code with a particular input exceeded the maximum allowed   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         execution time. LibFuzzer terminates the execution when it detects that processing  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         is taking too long, which typically suggests an infinite loop, excessive recursion, [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         or algorithmically inefficient code path that becomes problematic with specific     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         input patterns.                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Vulnerability Type                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         This issue represents a potential Denial of Service [1m([0mDoS[1m)[0m vulnerability. If an      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         attacker can craft inputs that trigger these long-running execution paths, they     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         could potentially hang the application or consume excessive computational           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         resources, making the service unavailable to legitimate users.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Important Observations                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **Timeout Occurrence**: The fuzzer successfully identified an input that causes  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the program to hang or run significantly longer than expected                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **Reproducibility**: LibFuzzer typically saves the input that triggered the      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         timeout, which should be available for reproduction and analysis                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Severity**: While not a memory corruption issue, timeout vulnerabilities can   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         be serious for production systems as they can lead to resource exhaustion           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Areas for Investigation                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         To gain a holistic understanding of this issue, the following parts of the codebase [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         should be investigated:                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **Fuzzing Harness Entry Points**: Review the fuzzing harness to understand what  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         functions and code paths are being tested, and which components receive the         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         fuzzer-generated input                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **Input Processing Functions**: Examine all functions that process external      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         input, particularly:                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Parsing routines                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Deserialization logic                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Input validation functions                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Data transformation operations                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Loop Constructs**: Identify and analyze all loops in the code path, checking   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         for:                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Loops with input-dependent termination conditions                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Nested loops where inner/outer loop bounds depend on input                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - While loops that may not have guaranteed termination                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. **Recursive Functions**: Review any recursive function calls that could lead to  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         deep recursion based on input characteristics                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. **Algorithmic Complexity**: Examine algorithms that may have poor worst-case     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         time complexity [1m([0me.g., [1;35mO[0m[1m([0mn²[1m)[0m, [1;35mO[0m[1m([0mn³[1m)[0m, or worse[1m)[0m that could be triggered by specially [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         crafted inputs                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m. **Resource Allocation Patterns**: Investigate operations that allocate or        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         process resources in proportion to input values, which could lead to excessive      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         processing time                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m. **State Machines and Parser Logic**: Review any state machine implementations or [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         complex parsing logic that might enter problematic states with certain input        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         patterns                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m. **External Dependencies**: Check if the code path involves calls to external     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         libraries or system calls that might block or take excessive time under certain     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         conditions                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The investigation should focus on tracing the execution path from the fuzzing       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         harness through the actual implementation to identify where the timeout occurs and  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         what input characteristics trigger this behavior.                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Analysis [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m857[0m[39m:                        charMatchCount = [0m[1;39m([0m[39m ch == E [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ? [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m : [0m[1;39m([0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m ch == N [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && [0m[1;39m([0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m858[0m[39m:                        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m search again for [0m[32m'endstream'[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m859[0m[39m:                        keyw = ENDSTREAM;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m860[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m861[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m862[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m863[0m[39m:            [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m864[0m[39m:            int contentBytes = [0m[1;35mMath.max[0m[1;39m([0m[39m [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, bIdx - charMatchCount [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m865[0m[39m:            [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m866[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m write buffer content until first matched char to output stream[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m867[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m contentBytes > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m[1;39m)[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m868[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m869[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mout.filter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstrmBuf, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, contentBytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m870[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m871[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m charMatchCount == keyw.length [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand following buffered content[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m874[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35msource.rewind[0m[1;39m([0m[39m bufSize - contentBytes [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m875[0m[39m:                break;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m876[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m877[0m[39m:            else [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m878[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m879[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m copy matched chars at start of buffer[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m880[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mSystem.arraycopy[0m[1;39m([0m[39m keyw, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, strmBuf, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, charMatchCount [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m881[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m            [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m882[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m883[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m this writes a lonely CR or drops trailing CR LF and LF[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m884[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mout.calculateLength[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m885[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBased on the evaluation report and code analysis, the timeout issue stems from [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmultiple vectors where malicious PDFs can cause excessive processing time:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Primary Vulnerabilities Identified:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Unbounded Recursion in Core Parsing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCRITICAL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mBaseParser.parseDirObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` has no depth tracking and recursively calls [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mparseCOSDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mparseCOSArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which call back to `[0m[1;35mparseDirObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor nested structures[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mCOSParser.checkPagesDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` recursively processes page trees with only [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcycle detection but no depth limit[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mPDNameTreeNode.getValue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` recursively traverses name trees with NO cycle [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetection or depth limits[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Unbounded Loop Iterations [0m[1;39m([0m[39mHIGH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mXrefParser.parseXrefTable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` allows unlimited xref entry counts, enabling [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmillions of iterations[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mBruteForceParser.bfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` scans entire files byte-by-byte when [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormal parsing fails[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mCOSParser.readUntilEndStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` reads arbitrarily large streams without size [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimits[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Object Stream Processing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mMEDIUM[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mPDFObjectStreamParser.parseAllObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` processes unlimited numbers of [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobjects in compressed streams without upper bound validation[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe codebase has a pattern of recursion depth protection in `PDFStreamEngine` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m-level limit[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but this protection is completely absent in the main parsing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfrastructure. Malicious PDFs can exploit deeply nested structures or circular [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreferences to cause stack overflow or excessive processing time.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Phase [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Add Recursion Depth Tracking to Core Parsing[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1.1[0m[39m Add depth tracking to BaseParser:**[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add a `protected int parsingDepth = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` field to `BaseParser`[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add a `protected static final int MAX_PARSING_DEPTH = [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m` constant [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmatching [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPDFStreamEngine's limit[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add helper methods:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  protected void [0m[1;35mincreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++parsingDepth > MAX_PARSING_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Maximum parsing depth exceeded: "[0m[39m + [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_PARSING_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  protected void [0m[1;35mdecreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      parsingDepth--;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1.2[0m[39m Instrument [0m[1;35mparseDirObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m recursion:**[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `[0m[1;35mBaseParser.parseDirObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m948[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add depth tracking around recursive [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Call `[0m[1;35mincreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at the start[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Wrap the entire method body in try-finally to call `[0m[1;35mdecreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe finally block[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - This protects against deep nesting through dictionaries and arrays[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1.3[0m[39m Instrument [0m[1;35mparseCOSDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m recursion:**[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `[0m[1;35mBaseParser.parseCOSDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m281[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add depth tracking:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Call `[0m[1;35mincreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` after creating the COSDictionary object [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m286[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Wrap the while loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m288[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m316[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and cleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m317[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m326[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in try-finally [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith `[0m[1;35mdecreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in finally[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - This tracks dictionary nesting depth[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1.4[0m[39m Instrument [0m[1;35mparseCOSArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m recursion:**[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `[0m[1;35mBaseParser.parseCOSArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m755[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add depth tracking:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Call `[0m[1;35mincreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` after creating the COSArray object [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter line [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m759[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Wrap the while loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m763[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m817[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and cleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m818[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m820[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in try-finally [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith `[0m[1;35mdecreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in finally[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - This tracks array nesting depth[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Phase [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Add Depth Limits to Tree Traversals[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m2.1[0m[39m Fix [0m[1;35mcheckPagesDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in COSParser:**[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modify the signature from `private int [0m[1;35mcheckPagesDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCOSDictionary [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpagesDict, Set<COSObject> set[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to add a depth parameter: `private int [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcheckPagesDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCOSDictionary pagesDict, Set<COSObject> set, int depth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add depth check at the start of the method:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MAX_PARSING_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Maximum page tree depth exceeded, truncating at depth [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, depth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Update the recursive call at line [0m[1;36m986[0m[39m to pass `depth + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`: `numberOfPages += [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcheckPagesDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mkidDictionary, set, depth + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Update the initial call at line [0m[1;36m946[0m[39m to pass depth [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m: `[0m[1;35mcheckPagesDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpages,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnew HashSet<>[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m2.2[0m[39m Fix [0m[1;35mgetValue[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in PDNameTreeNode:**[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add a private overload: `private T [0m[1;35mgetValue[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString name, int depth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException`[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Move the current implementation to this overload[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add depth check at the start:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > [0m[1;36m50[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Maximum name tree depth exceeded, returning null"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      return null;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Update the recursive call at line [0m[1;36m232[0m[39m to pass depth: `return [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mchildNode.getValue[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname, depth + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Change the public method at line [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m to delegate: `return [0m[1;35mgetValue[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Phase [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Add Resource Limits to Loop Operations[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m3.1[0m[39m Limit xref table entry counts:**[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `[0m[1;35mXrefParser.parseXrefTable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, add a constant `private static final int [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_XREF_ENTRIES = 10_000_000`[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After parsing `count` at line [0m[1;36m626[0m[39m, add validation:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcount < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || count > MAX_XREF_ENTRIES[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid or excessive xref entry count: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m, limiting to [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, count, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_XREF_ENTRIES[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      return false;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m3.2[0m[39m Add limits to object stream parsing:**[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `PDFObjectStreamParser` constructor or at line [0m[1;36m59[0m[39m where `[0m[35m/[0m[95mN[0m[39m` is read, add [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mn < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || n > 1_000_000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid object stream count: "[0m[39m + n[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m3.3[0m[39m Add size limits to stream reading:**[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `[0m[1;35mCOSParser.readUntilEndStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, add a maximum stream size check:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Add constant `private static final long MAX_STREAM_SIZE = 500L * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m500[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Track cumulative bytes read before line [0m[1;36m869[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - If cumulative size exceeds limit, throw IOException[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m3.4[0m[39m Add safety timeout to brute force scanning:**[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `[0m[1;35mBruteForceParser.bfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, add a check every [0m[1;36m10000[0m[39m iterations:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Track iteration count[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - If count exceeds a threshold [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m million[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, log warning and abort scanning[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - This prevents multi-gigabyte files from causing indefinite scanning[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Phase [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m: Thread-Safe Depth Tracking[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m4.1[0m[39m Make depth tracking thread-safe if needed:**[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If BaseParser instances can be used concurrently, change `parsingDepth` to use [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ThreadLocal<Integer>`[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- However, based on the `synchronized` keyword on `parseObjectDynamically` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m465[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, it appears parsing is meant to be single-threaded per parser instance[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep the simple integer field approach for performance[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Phase [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m: Testing Considerations[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m5.1[0m[39m Ensure backwards compatibility:**[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The depth limits should only affect maliciously crafted PDFs[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Normal PDFs rarely nest structures beyond [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m15[0m[39m levels[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A limit of [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmatching PDFStreamEngine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m provides substantial headroom[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The xref entry limit of [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m million is extremely generous for legitimate PDFs[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m5.2[0m[39m Error messages:**[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All limit exceptions should include clear messages indicating which limit was [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceeded[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Use INFO or WARN level logging before throwing exceptions to aid debugging[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m5.3[0m[39m Configuration options:**[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Consider making limits configurable via system properties:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.maxParsingDepth`[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.maxXrefEntries`[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.maxStreamSize`[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fall back to hardcoded defaults if not specified[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is the Optimal Approach:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Follows Existing Patterns:** The fix replicates the proven recursion depth [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprotection pattern already used in `PDFStreamEngine`, ensuring consistency across [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe codebase.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Minimal Invasiveness:** The changes are surgical - adding depth tracking [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout modifying the core parsing logic. The try-finally pattern ensures depth is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperly managed even during exceptions.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Defense in Depth:** Multiple protection layers [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrecursion depth, loop counts, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize limits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m provide comprehensive coverage against different timeout vectors.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Preserves Functionality:** Legitimate PDFs will be unaffected since:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Normal PDFs rarely exceed [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m15[0m[39m nesting levels[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Normal xref tables have thousands to tens of thousands of entries, not [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmillions[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The limits are set generously above typical use cases[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Evaluation Report:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Timeout Prevention:** Recursion depth limits prevent stack overflow and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexcessive call stack processing.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **DoS Mitigation:** Resource limits prevent attackers from crafting PDFs that [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsume excessive CPU time.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Early Detection:** Depth checks fail fast before consuming significant [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresources.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **[0m[3;91mFalse[0m[39m Positives:** Extremely complex but legitimate PDFs might hit limits[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation:** Set limits well above normal use [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m50[0m[39m for depth, 10M for xref [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentries[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation:** Make limits configurable via system properties[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Performance Impact:** Depth increment/decrement adds overhead to parsing[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation:** Simple integer operations are negligible compared to I/O and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobject creation[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation:** The try-finally pattern is JVM-optimized[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Existing Tests:** Some fuzz tests or stress tests might exceed limits[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation:** Review test failures and adjust limits or mark specific tests [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas expected exceptions[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Referenced Similar Solutions:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix directly mirrors the protection in `[0m[1;35mPDFStreamEngine.increaseLevel[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mDrawObject.process[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m72[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m77[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which successfully prevents deep recursion in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mform XObjects. This proven pattern is being extended to the parsing layer where it [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas missing.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Code Ranges for Implementation[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix strategy requires modifications to these files:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BaseParser.java`: Add depth [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtracking infrastructure[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/COSParser.java`: Fix [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheckPagesDictionary and readUntilEndStream[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/common/PDNameTreeNode.java`: Fix [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgetValue recursion[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/XrefParser.java`: Add xref [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcount validation[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFObjectStreamParser.java`: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd object count validation[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java`: Add [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miteration limits[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-                if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35misThisTheEnd.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && [0m[1;35msource.peek[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95mit[0m[39m could be a bad object in the array which is just skipped[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                    [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Corrupt array element at offset [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m, start offset: [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                    String isThisTheEnd = [0m[1;35mreadString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-        [0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
