[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Patch [0m[33mResult[0m[39m===[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===[0m[33mIssue[0m[39m===[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reports a [0m[32m"libFuzzer: timeout"[0m[39m error, indicating that the fuzzer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencountered a code path that takes an excessively long time to execute, exceeding [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe timeout threshold. A patch was attempted to address this issue by introducing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing depth limits and a maximum stream size constant. However, the patch [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresulted in compilation errors due to: [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m a duplicate declaration of the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`document` variable that already exists in the class, and [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m a reference to an [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mundefined `result` variable. The build failed before the timeout issue could be [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidated.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue presents as [0m[32m"ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout"[0m[39m, which indicates that during [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing operations, the code entered a state where processing took longer than the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfigured timeout period. This is a common symptom in PDF parsing where:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Deeply nested structures [0m[1;39m([0m[39marrays within arrays, dictionaries within dictionaries[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan lead to exponential processing time[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Malformed or maliciously crafted PDF files can trigger infinite or near-infinite [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Unbounded recursive parsing can consume excessive resources[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch introduces several modifications across two files:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**In COSParser.java:**[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds a constant `MAX_STREAM_SIZE = 500L * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m500MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to limit stream [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msizes[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**In BaseParser.java:**[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempts to add recursion depth tracking with the following changes:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Variable Declarations [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m93[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m96[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Attempts to declare `protected COSDocument document;` - this causes a [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation error because the variable already exists in the class[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adds `protected int parsingDepth = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;` to track current parsing depth[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adds `protected static final int MAX_PARSING_DEPTH = [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m;` as a threshold[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Modified getObjectFromPool Method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m270[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m275[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Changes the return statement from `return [0m[1;35mdocument.getObjectFromPool[0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`return result;`[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This causes a compilation error because `result` is not defined in scope[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **New Helper Methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m277[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m289[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mincreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`: Increments depth counter and throws IOException if [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_PARSING_DEPTH is exceeded[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mdecreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`: Decrements depth counter[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Modified parseCOSDictionary Method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m303[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m353[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wraps existing dictionary parsing logic in try-finally block[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Calls `[0m[1;35mincreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at the start[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Calls `[0m[1;35mdecreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in the finally block to ensure depth is [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdecremented even on exceptions[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Modified parseCOSArray Method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m785[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m856[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar pattern as parseCOSDictionary: wraps array parsing in try-finally with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth tracking[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensures depth counter is properly managed during array parsing[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Compilation Errors[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch produces two compilation errors:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m173[0m[39m - Duplicate variable declaration:**[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   variable document is already defined in class [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.BaseParser[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The `document` field already exists in the BaseParser class, so the patch's [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempt to redeclare it as `protected COSDocument document;` conflicts with the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting declaration.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m275[0m[39m - Undefined variable:**[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   cannot find symbol: variable result[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The patch changes the return statement to `return result;` but never defines [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhat `result` is. The original code returned `[0m[1;35mdocument.getObjectFromPool[0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich was replaced incorrectly.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Further Investigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a holistic view of the timeout issue and develop a proper fix, the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfollowing areas should be investigated:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **BaseParser.java existing structure:**[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine the current declaration and usage of the `document` field[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Understand the original implementation of the `getObjectFromPool` method to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetermine the correct return value[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review if there are other recursive parsing methods that should also include [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth tracking[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **COSParser.java:**[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Investigate how `MAX_STREAM_SIZE` constant should be utilized [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe patch [0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause of Timeout Issue[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe libFuzzer timeout occurs due to unbounded recursion when parsing deeply nested [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPDF structures [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdictionaries within dictionaries, arrays within arrays[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase lacks depth limits in the parsing layer, allowing malicious or malformed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPDFs to cause exponential processing time.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Comprehensive Fix Strategy[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Add Recursion Depth Tracking to BaseParser[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BaseParser.java`[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**After line [0m[1;36m168[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter the existing `protected COSDocument document;` [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclaration[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add two new fields:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `private int parsingDepth = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;` - tracks current parsing recursion depth[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `private static final int MAX_PARSING_DEPTH = [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m;` - maximum allowed depth [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mconsistent with PDFStreamEngine's level checking pattern[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**After the `getObjectFromPool` method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter line [0m[1;36m271[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add two new helper [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethods:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprotected void [0m[1;35mincreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++parsingDepth > MAX_PARSING_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Maximum parsing depth exceeded: "[0m[39m + [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_PARSING_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprotected void [0m[1;35mdecreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    parsingDepth--;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparsingDepth < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mLOG.error[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Parsing depth is negative: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, parsingDepth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Important**: Do NOT modify the existing `document` field declaration or the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`getObjectFromPool` method's return statement. These caused the compilation errors [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the last patch.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Modify parseCOSDictionary Method[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BaseParser.java` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines [0m[1;36m281[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m328[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWrap the entire method body [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter creating the COSDictionary object at line [0m[1;36m287[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min a try-finally block:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call `[0m[1;35mincreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` right after line [0m[1;36m287[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mobj.setDirect[0m[1;39m([0m[39misDirect[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Wrap lines [0m[1;36m288[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m327[0m[39m in a try block[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add a finally block that calls `[0m[1;35mdecreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep all existing error handling logic intact[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis ensures that even if parsing fails or returns early [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m302[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m313[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth counter is properly decremented.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Modify parseCOSArray Method[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BaseParser.java` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines [0m[1;36m755[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m822[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApply the same try-finally pattern:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call `[0m[1;35mincreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` right after line [0m[1;36m761[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Wrap lines [0m[1;36m762[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m821[0m[39m in a try block[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add a finally block that calls `[0m[1;35mdecreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep all existing error handling logic, including the explicit recursion check at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m800[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m802[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Add Stream Size Limit to COSParser[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/COSParser.java`[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Add constant around line [0m[1;36m78[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnear STRMBUFLEN[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `private static final long MAX_STREAM_SIZE = 500L * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m;` - 500MB limit[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Modify validateStreamLength method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m900[0m[39m, after the negative length [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd a new check before line [0m[1;36m901[0m[39m:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstreamLength > MAX_STREAM_SIZE[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Stream length [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m exceeds maximum allowed size [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m bytes, start [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mposition: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             streamLength, MAX_STREAM_SIZE, originOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return false;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis prevents attempting to parse extremely large streams that could cause [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeouts. When validation fails, `parseCOSStream` automatically falls back to the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msafer `readUntilEndStream` method.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This Approach is Optimal[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Follows Existing Patterns**: The depth tracking mechanism mirrors the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuccessful pattern used in `PDFStreamEngine` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlevel tracking with increase/decrease[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethods[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, ensuring consistency with the codebase[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Minimal Invasiveness**: Only adds new fields and methods without modifying [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting logic, reducing the risk of breaking functionality[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Proper Resource Cleanup**: Using try-finally blocks ensures the depth counter [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis always decremented, preventing counter corruption that could mask subsequent [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeeply nested structures[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Defense in Depth**: Combines two complementary protections:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Recursion depth limits prevent stack overflow and exponential time complexity [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min nested structures[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stream size limits prevent memory exhaustion and timeout from extremely large [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstreams[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Fail-Safe Behavior**: When limits are exceeded, the parser throws descriptive [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOExceptions or falls back to safer parsing methods rather than hanging [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindefinitely[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Preserves Existing Logic[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **No modifications to core parsing logic**: The while loops, error recovery, and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn paths remain unchanged[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **No changes to method signatures**: All modifications are internal, maintaining [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAPI compatibility[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Existing error handling preserved**: All LOG.warn calls, early returns, and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception catches remain functional[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Test compatibility**: The depth limit of [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m is reasonable for legitimate PDFs [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mmatching the existing limit in DrawObject.java[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so existing tests should pass[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Issues[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Compilation Errors**: Fixed by NOT redeclaring `document` and NOT modifying [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`getObjectFromPool`'s return statement[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Timeout Issue**: Addressed by preventing unbounded recursion through depth [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtracking and limiting stream sizes[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Resource Safety**: The try-finally pattern ensures proper cleanup even during [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceptions[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Legitimate deeply nested PDFs might be rejected**: [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: The limit of [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m levels is generous [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexceeds typical PDF nesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand matches existing limits in the codebase[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If needed, the constant can be made configurable through system properties[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Large but legitimate streams might be rejected**:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: 500MB is a very large limit that should accommodate legitimate use[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcases[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fallback to `readUntilEndStream` provides an alternative parsing path[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Performance overhead from depth checking**:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: Simple integer increment/decrement operations have negligible [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mperformance impact compared to the parsing operations themselves[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **PDFStreamEngine.level**: Lines [0m[1;36m92[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m1146[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1177[0m[39m show the exact pattern of level [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtracking with increase/decrease methods[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **DrawObject.java line [0m[1;36m73[0m[39m**: Shows checking `level > [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m` to prevent stack [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow, validating our choice of MAX_PARSING_DEPTH = [0m[1;36m50[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **parseCOSArray line [0m[1;36m800[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m802[0m[39m**: Already has explicit recursion prevention logic, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshowing the codebase's awareness of recursion issues[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaximum stream size constant to prevent infinite recursion and excessive resource [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsumption. However, after applying the patch, the timeout error persists, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating that the modifications were insufficient to resolve the underlying [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mperformance issue causing the timeout.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reports an [0m[32m"ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout"[0m[39m which occurs when the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing harness exercises the codebase and encounters an execution path that takes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtoo long to complete. This timeout indicates that the code is either:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Entering an infinite or near-infinite loop[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Processing extremely large amounts of data inefficiently[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Encountering deeply nested structures that cause excessive recursion or iteration[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch introduces several defensive mechanisms across three files in the PDF [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing infrastructure:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. COSParser.java modifications:**[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds a constant `MAX_STREAM_SIZE` set to 500MB [0m[1;39m([0m[39m500L * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This constant is declared but not actively used in the visible patch, suggesting [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit may be intended for future stream size validation[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. BaseParser.java modifications:**[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introduces a `parsingDepth` instance variable initialized to [0m[1;36m0[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds a constant `MAX_PARSING_DEPTH` set to [0m[1;36m50[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Implements two new methods:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `[0m[1;35mincreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`: Increments the depth counter and throws an [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException if the maximum depth is exceeded[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `[0m[1;35mdecreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`: Decrements the depth counter with error logging for [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnegative values[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Parser method modifications:**[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch wraps two critical parsing methods with depth tracking:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **`[0m[1;35mparseCOSDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method:** The entire dictionary parsing logic is wrapped[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min a try-finally block that calls `[0m[1;35mincreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at the start and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mdecreaseParsingDepth[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in the finally block. This ensures depth tracking even [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen exceptions occur.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **`[0m[1;35mparseCOSArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method:** Similarly wrapped with the same depth tracking [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern, ensuring that array parsing respects the maximum depth constraint.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch essentially implements a recursion depth limiter for nested PDF [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructures [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdictionaries and arrays[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which are common sources of infinite [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecursion in malformed or malicious PDF files.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the timeout error persists. This suggests several [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpossibilities:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout may be occurring in parsing code paths not covered by the depth [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimiting [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., stream parsing, other object types[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The maximum depth of [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m may still be too high for the time constraints of the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout may be caused by iterative loops rather than recursive calls[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Other performance bottlenecks exist that are not addressed by recursion depth [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimiting[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Further Investigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo understand the root cause of the timeout and develop an effective solution, the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfollowing areas should be investigated:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Stream Parsing Logic:** The `MAX_STREAM_SIZE` constant was added but not [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mutilized in the visible patch. The actual stream parsing implementation in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCOSParser.java should be examined to determine if unbounded stream reading is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurring.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Other Parsing Methods:** Methods beyond `[0m[1;35mparseCOSDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mparseCOSArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` should be analyzed, including:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mparseDirObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - called within array parsing[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stream content parsing methods[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Object reference resolution logic[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any other methods that process PDF structures[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Iterative Loops:** The while loops in both `[0m[1;35mparseCOSDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mparseCOSArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` should be examined for conditions that could cause excessive [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations with specific input patterns.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Object Pool and Reference Resolution:** The `[0m[1;35mgetObjectFromPool[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobject key resolution mechanism should be investigated for potential circular [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreferences or expensive lookups.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Input Characteristics:** Analysis of the specific fuzzer input that causes the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout would reveal which parsing path is problematic. Fuzzer logs or crash [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39martifacts may contain the triggering input.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Performance Profiling:** Instrumenting the code to identify which specific [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod or loop is consuming the most time during the timeout scenario would [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpinpoint the exact bottleneck.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Recovery Logic:** The error recovery code paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreadUntilEndOfCOSDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m should be examined as they may enter expensive [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops when processing malformed input.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Additional Issue Log[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
